VESICA PISCIS

GEOMETRY CARES EXACTLY WHAT SHAPE
A VENN DIAGRAM IS.

HOW FAR DO YOU THINK TWO CIRCLES
SHOULD OVERLAP?

ONE ANSWER IS TO GO HALFWAY, 
SO THE CIRCLES INTERSECT EACH OTHER
IN THEIR MIDDLES.

THE SHAPE OF THE CENTER IS CALLED
"VESICA PISCIS" AND CAN BE FOUND IN
GEOMETRY, ART, AND ARCHITECTURE.
